claim.claim-text:
1. A method for processing video data for delivery to a remote wireless device comprising:
receiving video data from a video source;
receiving position and motion information regarding a current location of the remote wireless device;
based upon the position and motion information regarding the remote wireless device at the current location, determining a Quality of Service (QoS) to be available for servicing of transmissions to the remote wireless device based on a rate of motion of the remote wireless device;
determining video processing parameters based upon the video data and the QoS for the current location;
processing the video data based upon the video processing parameters to produce an output video stream for transmission at the current location;
producing a QoS map for display on the remote wireless device;
transmitting the output video stream for delivery to the remote wireless device along with the QoS map;
based upon the current location and rate of motion, anticipating a future location of the remote wireless device; and
based on the anticipated future location and historical QoS, determining an anticipated QoS for the anticipated future location and transmitting the video stream and the QoS map based on the anticipated QoS when the remote wireless device enters the anticipated future location, so as to transmit the output video stream to the remote wireless device based on changing QoS, as the remote wireless device changes locations, and in which the QoS map to indicate alternative QoS available to the remote wireless device based on different rate of motion of the remote wireless device.

8. The method of claim 7, wherein the wireless transmission parameters are selected from the group consisting of:
slot assignment parameters;
channel assignment parameters;
transmit power allocation parameters;
beam forming parameters;
Multi-Input-Multi-Output (MIMO) parameters;
modulation parameters; and
coding parameters.

11. A video processing system comprising:
a communications interface; and
video processing circuitry coupled to the communications interface that, in conjunction with the communications interface is operable to:
receive video data from a video source;
receive position and motion information regarding a current location of a remote wireless device;
based upon the position and motion information regarding the remote wireless device at the current location, determine a Quality of Service (QoS) to be available for servicing of transmissions to the remote wireless device based on a rate of motion of the remote wireless device;
determine video processing parameters based upon the video data and the QoS for the current location;
process the video data based upon the video processing parameters to produce an output video stream for transmission at the current location;
produce a QoS map for display on the remote wireless device;
transmit the output video stream for delivery to the remote wireless device along with the QoS map;
based upon the current location and rate of motion, anticipate a future location of the remote wireless device; and
based on the anticipated future location and historical QoS, determine an anticipated QoS for the anticipated future location and transmit the video stream and the QoS map based on the anticipated QoS when the remote wireless device enters the anticipated future location, so as to transmit the output video stream to the remote wireless device based on changing QoS, as the remote wireless device changes locations, and in which the QoS map to indicate alternative QoS available to the remote wireless device based on different rate of motion of the remote wireless device.

18. The video processing system of claim 17, wherein the wireless transmission parameters are selected from the group consisting of:
slot assignment parameters;
channel assignment parameters;
transmit power allocation parameters;
beam forming parameters;
Multi-Input-Multi-Output (MIMO) parameters;
modulation parameters; and
coding parameters.
